															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kakroom" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2198340); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2198340&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227504" alt="Kakroom" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2198340)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kakroom" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2198340); return false;" >Kakroom</a></span> <span class="odate time_1478728927 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">09 Nov 2016 22:02</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2688279">
									

<p>I've been checking all day for this. Literally popped off the page, popped back onto Recently Created, and there it was.</p>
<p>Edit: Post-reading stuff.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>AGUS<br />
How could it be otherwise?<br />
[/=]</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>[[=]]<br />
THE MAN</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I can't tell if those knobbly bits are intended or broken formatting. Just putting it here in case they were oversights.</p>
<p>I was also about to question this being in the format of a play, but then I realized, 'oh, performance,' and it made more sense.</p>
<p>All in all&#8230; I don't really know how to take this. In a good way.</p>
<p>There's no questioning that as a whole this has been well written, all-encompassing, and everything an 001 proposal should be. There's so much more weird and eldritch here than I've gotten out of any other of the submissions, and I think I might have enjoyed it more than a few, but in a different capacity. It's all so bizarrely fatalistic at the last, which is a characteristic I'd never think to associate with the Foundation; 1 titling his message 'the end,' an 05 committing suicide, etc.. But it provides a very compelling alternative view of how things might go down when they face an insurmountable threat. Or maybe threat is the wrong the word.</p>
<p>In any case, I'm going to upvote.</p>

							</div>

								
