			<div class="content" id="post-content-2688311">
									

<p>So we're finally at the end. It's odd; each individual piece of the story seemed fantastic on its own merits, but putting it in the context of a larger series served to detract from it. This final piece is sufficiently oblique that I didn't understand most of it. The ending was fine, but it feels as though this is roughly 2/3 through a story that will presumably never be finished. Gonna re-read later, but unless some lightning bolt of clarity strikes the heck out of me, the vote will remain -1.</p>
<p>Props for trying something very different on a variety of levels, but this just did not work for me on most of them.</p>

							</div>

								
					
