<p>SCP-2303 is sort of a place where wrong ideas appear, or at least ideas that are very much better left to die.</p>
<p>The Man at the Threshold is one of those ideas that appeared there.</p>
<p>The implication, to me, is that the 001 society of humans aren't right, in a sense. They might be perfect from some definitions&#8212; but they are completely devoid of any hope. They cannot conceive of anything beyond the hells they've made. They lost whatever humanity they might have had.</p>
<p>Honestly the hope i'm implying is less that anyone will survive&#8212; but more that the conclusion that caused 001 to become this way is erroneous.</p>

