		<div class="post" id="post-2688377">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2688377)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2688377">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227504" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;" >djkaktus</a></span> <span class="odate time_1478738334 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 Nov 2016 00:38</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2688377">
									

<p>I have reserved comments on most of these, for the sake of retrospect. I'd rather my thoughts be based on the whole than on any single thought I had throughout.</p>
<p>And yet, I can't help but now look back and see the path we took to get here, step by step. It's not an incredibly long piece, all in all. Not compared to other articles on the wiki. But it may as well have been a lifetime.</p>
<p>I had thought that you, Kalinin, might have made this a character focused affair. You do, after all, have some of the finest characterization of any author currently writing here. And it was there, no doubt, in parts. We got glimpses of real people.</p>
<p>But in the end it wasn't characterization that drove the conclusion, but imagery. And gods, what imagery. Lights in the sky, screams and twisted flesh and the horror of the great and terrible end. The Planet of Hands.</p>
<p>People ask, often enough, what should be required for a 001. Is it the first thing the Foundation found, like Mann's or Gears'? Is it a story about how the Foundation was formed, like Bright's and Roget's? Is it something greater than that, something out of universe like SAndrewSwann's? Or maybe it's something great and terrible, like Clef's angel, or the Children of San Marco, or a girl made into a God, or a mountain of machines, the universe, or even the Foundation itself? I can't give an answer to that, and my throwaway response is that we'll know it when we see it. Here, I see it.</p>
<p>After all, what's more fitting to hold the Foundation's most esteemed position than it's final, agonizing breath?</p>
<p>Fuck if I know. +1</p>

							</div>

								
					
